## Windows 2.0 — what it has, what it's missing

### What Windows has that Mac lacks

Windows 2.0 actually leads Mac in several features:

- **Folding** — collapse document sections by heading. Essential for navigating long mythology manuscripts
- **Dynamic Outline** — heading-based sidebar navigation for large documents
- **Writing Goals** — word-count targets per document
- **Snippets** — multi-line text expansion shortcuts, useful for recurring Markdown patterns or verse structures
- **Hunspell dictionaries** — expandable with custom language files

### What Windows is missing compared to Mac

| Feature | Windows | Mac |
|---------|---------|-----|
| Focus Mode (Sentence / Paragraph / Typewriter) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Dark Mode | ✅ | ✅ |
| Content Blocks | ✅ | ✅ |
| Style Check (En, De, Fr) | ✅ | ✅ (+ Es) |
| Syntax Highlight | ✅ English only | ✅ 6 languages |
| PDF / Word / HTML Export | ✅ | ✅ |
| Custom Templates | ✅ | ✅ |
| iA Fonts (Mono / Duo / Quattro) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Folding | ✅ exclusive | ❌ |
| Dynamic Outline | ✅ exclusive | ❌ |
| Writing Goals | ✅ exclusive | ❌ |
| Snippets | ✅ exclusive | ❌ |
| Authorship / AI Tracking | ❌ coming 2026 | ✅ |
| Wikilinks | ❌ no timeline | ✅ |
| Blog Publishing | ❌ | ✅ |
| Global Document Search | ❌ | ✅ |

**Most significant gaps for a poet's workflow:**

Wikilinks (`[[document links]]`) — Mac and iOS only, no announced Windows timeline. These would allow linking between mythology entries, character references, and poem cycles.

Authorship / AI Tracking — confirmed arriving on Windows in 2026. Will let Evan mark which passages were AI-assisted versus hand-composed, with visual differentiation in the editor.

---

## Focus Mode — the core feature for stream and for writing

Focus Mode is iA Writer's signature feature. It highlights the active text and dims everything else — creating a dramatic visual effect that looks exceptional on camera and genuinely improves writing flow.

### Three options

**Sentence Focus** — highlights only the current sentence at full contrast (solid white in dark mode) while dimming all surrounding text to gray. The highlight shifts as the cursor moves. Most visually dramatic for streaming — viewers see exactly which words are being composed.

**Paragraph Focus** — same behavior but highlights the entire active paragraph. Better for editing passes where more context is needed.

**Typewriter Scrolling** — keeps the cursor vertically centered on screen at all times. Does not dim any text. Can be **combined with Sentence or Paragraph Focus** — this is the ideal streaming configuration: active line highlighted, centered, everything else dimmed.

### Recommended streaming configuration

Enable all three simultaneously: **Focus → Sentence** + **Typewriter Scrolling** + **Full Screen (`F11`)**. In dark mode, this creates a completely clean canvas — nothing visible except the poem and the cursor.

iA recommends toggling Focus Mode **off during editing passes** — the vertical centering behavior can conflict with text selection, causing screen jumping.

### Keyboard shortcuts

| Action | Windows | Mac |
|--------|---------|-----|
| Toggle Focus Mode | `Ctrl+D` | `⌘D` |
| Toggle Syntax Highlight | `Shift+Ctrl+D` | `⇧⌘D` |

Focus Mode works identically on Windows and Mac. All three options are fully available on Windows 2.0.

