## OBS configuration for streaming iA Writer

No documentation exists of someone using iA Writer with OBS for live poetry streaming — E.I. Werner is a pioneer in this space. The app's design characteristics make it exceptionally well-suited for broadcast.

### Why iA Writer looks exceptional on stream

Dark mode + Sentence Focus + Typewriter Scrolling + full-screen creates a cinematic writing aesthetic: text on a dark background, active sentence glowing white, surrounding text faded to gray, blue cursor blinking at center-screen. Nothing else visible. iA Writer users frequently describe the effect as meditative and visually striking.

### OBS source setup

Use **Window Capture** (not Display Capture) and select the iA Writer window. This captures only iA Writer without exposing other desktop elements, allowing webcam and chat overlays without covering text.

**Critical:** Set both OBS Base Canvas Resolution and Output Resolution to **1920×1080**. Matching resolutions prevents downscaling blur that destroys text readability.

Use **Bilinear** downscale filter — it produces sharper text than Lanczos, which adds dithering that blurs fonts.

Use **NVENC encoder** (AERO X16 has RTX 5070) — offloads encoding from CPU to GPU.

Set to **30fps** — text content doesn't benefit from 60fps, and saved bandwidth improves per-frame quality.

Set video bitrate to **4500–6000 kbps**.

### iA Writer settings optimized for streaming

| Setting | Value | Reason |
|---------|-------|--------|
| Appearance | Dark Mode | Professional; reduces eye strain for viewers |
| Focus Mode | Sentence + Typewriter | Centers action; highlights active line |
| Font | iA Writer Mono | Crispest text on stream |
| Font size | As large as comfortable | Viewers watch at 720p or smaller — go bigger than feels right at desktop |
| Characters per line | 64 | Fewer characters = larger individual characters on stream |
| View | Full-screen (`F11`) | Removes all UI chrome |
| Toolbar | Hidden (Settings → General → Toolbar → Never) | Clean visual |

**Validation step:** Record a 30-second test clip, then watch it on a phone at 720p. If text is unreadable, increase font size further. Streaming text requires significantly larger sizes than comfortable desktop reading.

### Natural clip moments when streaming iA Writer

The clip is never the typing. The clip moments are: reading a completed line aloud, calling a sprint goal complete, reacting honestly to what was just written, explaining a mythology decision. iA Writer's Focus Mode makes these moments visually clean — when the cursor stops and you look at the camera, the entire frame goes quiet.

---

## The three fonts — and which one to use for poetry

All three iA Writer fonts are modifications of **IBM Plex Mono**, redesigned by iA with custom letterforms. They are variable fonts that adjust optical weight dynamically based on font size, screen density, and light/dark mode. The fonts are **open-source on GitHub** under the SIL Open Font License and can be downloaded for use in other applications.

| Font | Character widths | Character per line | Best for |
|------|-----------------|-------------------|---------|
| **Mono** | 1 (all equal) | Fewest | **Poetry, stream, verse composition** |
| **Duo** | 2 (1× and 1.5×) | Medium | General prose, mixed content |
| **Quattro** | 4 (0.5× to 1.5×) | Most | Fast reading, long-form prose |

**iA Writer Mono is the correct choice for verse.** Perfect character alignment ensures indentation carries meaning — critical for structured epic poetry or any form where visual spacing matters. The deliberate typewriter pace matches the reflective rhythm of poetry composition. On stream, Mono's uniform character width produces the crispest, most readable text at any resolution.

Custom fonts cannot be used in the editor — only Mono, Duo, and Quattro are available. Custom fonts can be used in Preview and export through custom HTML/CSS templates.

