## Style Check and Syntax Highlight

**Style Check** flags filler words, redundancies, and clichés in real time. Identified words appear **grayed out with a strikethrough** in the editor — showing how text reads without them. Double-click a struck-through word to select it for deletion. Nothing is automatically removed. Runs entirely locally — no internet required.

Categories flagged: filler words ("actually," "really," "very," "just," "basically" — hundreds tracked), redundancies ("completely finished," "free gift"), clichés. Custom patterns can be created via Settings → Style Check.

Available on Windows in **English, German, and French**.

**Syntax Highlight** applies colors to parts of speech: adjectives brown, nouns red, adverbs purple, verbs blue, conjunctions green. Individual categories can be toggled independently. Pairs powerfully with Focus Mode — dim surrounding text, then color-code the active sentence's parts of speech.

Available on Windows in **English only** (Mac supports six languages).

Both features appear only in the editor. Never visible in Preview, exports, or printed documents.

| Action | Windows | Mac |
|--------|---------|-----|
| Toggle Style Check | `Alt+Shift+Ctrl+D` | `⌥⇧⌘D` |
| Toggle Syntax Highlight | `Shift+Ctrl+D` | `⇧⌘D` |

