## Content Blocks — assembling long manuscripts from modular files

Content Blocks embed the content of one file directly into another. This is the key feature for managing a long epic poetry manuscript — individual cantos, books, or mythology entries live as separate `.md` files and assemble into a master document.

Syntax: place a forward slash and filename on an empty line:

```
/once-mother.md
/once-brother.md
/once-war.md
```

Supported file types: `.md` / `.txt` (embed full text), `.csv` (render as Markdown table), images (display inline), source code (code block).

Content Blocks resolve in Preview and are included in all exports (PDF, Word, HTML, Markdown). To add: drag a file from the Library into the editor, or type `/` followed by the filename — autocomplete suggests matches.

**Content Blocks are fully available on Windows.**

---

## Authorship — tracking AI vs. human text (coming to Windows 2026)

Authorship distinguishes human-composed text from AI-generated content. Introduced in iA Writer 7, it tracks the **origin of text entry** — not AI detection algorithms. All processing is local, no text leaves the device.

**How it works:** Copy text from an AI tool, right-click in iA Writer, select "Paste As" and choose the author (e.g., "Other/AI"). Existing text can be reassigned by selecting it and choosing from the Authors menu.

**Visual appearance after November 2025 redesign:** AI-generated text appears in a **rainbow color gradient**. Human collaborator text appears in distinct per-author colors. Your own text stays full contrast. Reference material appears dimmed gray.

Authorship metadata is stored at the end of the plain-text file, invisible in the editor. Metadata is **automatically stripped on export** — it is a writing-phase tool only.

**Not available on Windows yet — confirmed arriving in 2026.** Currently Mac, iPhone, iPad only.

