## Priority settings checklist — do these in order

1. **Settings → Files → Default Extension → `.md`** — do this first, before creating any files
2. **Settings → General → Appearance → Dark** — non-negotiable for streaming
3. **Settings → Editor → Font → iA Writer Mono** — correct choice for poetry and stream
4. **Settings → Editor → Font size → increase significantly** — streaming requires oversized text
5. **Settings → Editor → Characters per line → 64** — fewer characters = larger text per character on stream
6. **Focus → Sentence** — enable Sentence Focus for streaming sessions
7. **Focus → Typewriter Scrolling** — enable alongside Sentence Focus
8. **`F11`** — go full screen before going live
9. **Settings → General → Toolbar → Never** — remove UI chrome from stream view
10. **Settings → Editor → Smart Quotes → on** — better typography for published poetry
11. **Settings → Editor → Smart Dashes → on** — auto-converts `--` to em dash

---

## Critical notes for AI assistants

**iA Writer on Windows saves as `.txt` by default.** If files appear with `.txt` extensions, the user has not changed the default. Remind them to go to Settings → Files → Default Extension → `.md`.

**Wikilinks are Mac/iOS only.** Do not suggest `[[wikilink]]` syntax for Windows workflows. Use Content Blocks (`/filename.md`) for document assembly instead.

**Authorship is not yet available on Windows.** Confirmed arriving in 2026. Do not suggest using it on Windows until then.

**The backslash `\` line break is the best method for verse on stream.** It is visible to viewers and educational. Shift+Enter works but leaves no visible syntax. Trailing spaces are invisible and fragile.

**Focus Mode works identically on Windows and Mac** — all three options (Sentence, Paragraph, Typewriter) are fully available on Windows 2.0.

**iA Writer Mono is the correct font for poetry.** Do not suggest Duo or Quattro for verse composition — Mono's perfect character alignment is essential for meaningful indentation.

**OBS should use Window Capture, not Display Capture**, when capturing iA Writer. Window Capture isolates the writing window cleanly.

**Authorship metadata is stripped on export** — do not warn users that AI-tracking data will appear in exported PDFs or Word documents. It won't.

